{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778344729,"nonce":"bKb5W5JI93uD2nA4Jz3mm9vNOTc=","title":"Reorganize results/ folder hierarchy — cloud-provider subdirs and ad-hoc figure paths","message":"The results/ folder has grown chaotic. The recent _artifacts vs results split (about what gets committed) was the right call but did not address layout. Concrete pain points:\n\n- **Cloud-provider directory names are leaking into structure**: results/part2_5/runpod/\u003cexp\u003e/... — runpod/ is irrelevant to where results belong; it just reflects where the run happened to execute. Per CLAUDE.md \"Cloud-provider directory names are NOT meaningful,\" but the convention is being violated for new experiments.\n- **Inconsistent nesting depth**: some experiments live at results/\u003cexp\u003e/, others at results/part2_5/\u003cexp\u003e/, others under results/part2_5/runpod/\u003cexp\u003e/. No principled rule about when to nest under a phase prefix vs not.\n- **Figure paths are ad hoc**: figures/\u003cname\u003e/ subdirectories exist alongside spec.json, run.json, notes.md siblings without a stable pattern.\n- **Pre-migration legacy paths are mixed in with new conventions**, making the layout hard to navigate.\n\nGoal: a documented, uniform layout so a new agent (or human) can find where things go without precedent-archaeology. Keep this lightweight — the reorganization is about hierarchy and naming, not about what gets committed (that part already works).\n\nDefer concrete proposal until the next time we have a natural break in research work. Filing now to capture the concern.","files":null}]}